From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0057/N] jvmFlagConstraintsGC.cpp: skip TLAB upper-bound check when max_size uninitialized

`MinTLABSizeConstraintFunc` and `TLABSizeConstraintFunc` check
`value <= ThreadLocalAllocBuffer::max_size() * HeapWordSize`. The
upper bound `_max_size` is set later by `Universe::initialize_heap`
via `set_max_size(heap->max_tlab_size())`. On Linux the ergonomic
constraint checks happen to fire *after* `set_max_size`; on
CheriBSD/purecap they fire before, and `max_size()` returns 0 (release
mode hides the debug assert). The MinTLABSize default 2048 then fails
`2048 <= 0`, blocking VM startup.

Skip the upper-bound check when `max_size() == 0` (i.e., not yet
initialized). The same constraint will be re-checked when TLABs are
actually used.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0057)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/jvmFlagConstraintsGC.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/jvmFlagConstraintsGC.cpp
@@ -352,7 +352,10 @@
                         value, ThreadLocalAllocBuffer::alignment_reserve_in_bytes());
     return JVMFlag::VIOLATES_CONSTRAINT;
   }
-  if (value > (ThreadLocalAllocBuffer::max_size() * HeapWordSize)) {
+  // Skip upper-bound check if max_size is not yet initialized.
+  // GC's set_max_size runs after flag-constraint validation.
+  if (ThreadLocalAllocBuffer::max_size() != 0 &&
+      value > (ThreadLocalAllocBuffer::max_size() * HeapWordSize)) {
     JVMFlag::printError(verbose,
                         "MinTLABSize (" SIZE_FORMAT ") must be "
                         "less than or equal to ergonomic TLAB maximum (" SIZE_FORMAT ")\n",
@@ -372,7 +375,8 @@
                           value, MinTLABSize);
       return JVMFlag::VIOLATES_CONSTRAINT;
     }
-    if (value > (ThreadLocalAllocBuffer::max_size() * HeapWordSize)) {
+    if (ThreadLocalAllocBuffer::max_size() != 0 &&
+        value > (ThreadLocalAllocBuffer::max_size() * HeapWordSize)) {
       JVMFlag::printError(verbose,
                           "TLABSize (" SIZE_FORMAT ") must be "
                           "less than or equal to ergonomic TLAB maximum size (" SIZE_FORMAT ")\n",
